text: Kaustinen is a municipality in Central Ostrobothnia, Finland. It had 4,293 people living there in January 2014. The municipalities next to it are Halsua, Kokkola, Kruunupyy and Veteli. The municipality was established in 1868. == Other websites == * The official page Category:Municipalities of Central Ostrobothnia Category:1868 establishments in Finland
